stix:Indicator.indicator:Description:
The email body contained a link that directs to:
http://gallosport.com/list/default.html?<UNIQUE ID>

The malware associated with this activity may be a CTFMON variant.  The suspected variant may be detected with the following rules provided by the reporting U.S. government agency:

To detect the invalid X-Mailers used in this campaign (note that spam, in addition to spear-phishing will also be detected), the following SNORT signature may be used:

alert tcp any any -> any any (msg:"INVALID_XMAILER_MS_OUTLOOK_5589"; sid:
12345; content:"X-Mailer: Microsoft Outlook Express 6.00.2900.5589";)

If the same first stage implant is being used in this campaign, as in a previous campaign, activity involving the CTFMON Version 4 implant can be identified using the following signatures:

alert tcp any any <> any $HTTP_PORTS (msg:"CTFMONv4_DROPPER_CALLOUT";
flow:established,to_server; content:"GET"; http_method; content:"/blk"; http_uri;
pcre:"/^\/blk\d{2}\.htm$/U"; sid:1234;)

alert tcp any any -> any $WEB_PORTS (msg:"CTFMONv4_IMPLANT_CALLOUT"; sid:1234;
flow:established,to_server; content:"GET"; http_method; content:"/xdot/index";
fast_pattern: only; http_uri; pcre:"/^\/xdot\/index(?:1|33|34)_[0-9]{1,16}\.html$/U";)
